===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{liushu|p}} of water flowing; sometimes written as the variant [[氺]] (e.g., [[泰]], [[录]], and [[黎]]). Next to a character, it is compressed and stylized into [[氵]] (which is unrelated to [[冫]]).

Compare {{och-l|川}} and its variant [[巛]]. Compare also [[永]] and its cognate [[𠂢]]. See also the bottom part of [[原]] in its original version ([[厡]]).

===Etymology 1===
{{wp|zh:,yue:,lzh:,gan:,hak:súi,cdo:cūi,nan:chúi,wuu:}}
Here are some proposals: 
* {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*lwi(j)||[[flow]]; [[stream]]}} ({{zh-ref|Benedict, 1974}}; {{zh-ref|Coblin, 1986}}; {{zh-ref|Handel, 1998}}; {{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}; STEDT). Cognate with {{cog|lus|lui||stream; [[brook]]; [[river]]}}, {{cog|ctd|||tr=luːi³|stream; river}}, {{cog|kac|lawi||to flow (as [[water]])}}.
**{{cog|och|水|tr=*lhuiʔ}}, as reconstructed by Schuessler, is {{cog|sit}} root's endoactive derivation with suffix ''*-ʔ'', meaning "that which is flowing"; its voiceless initial suggests the presence of a nominalizing prefix ''*k-'' or ''*s-''. Another derivative from the {{cog|sit}} root is possibly {{m|och|泫|tr=winʔ|t=to flow}} (minimally reconstructed).
**Compare also areal etyma {{cog|aav-pro|*loːjʔ||to [[wade]]; to [[swim]]}} and {{cog|tai-pro|*loːjᴬ||to swim}}.
*{{zh-ref|Gong (1995)}} reconstructs {{cog|och|-}} ''*hljədx'' and compares it to {{cog|bo|ཆུ||tr=chu|water}}, which STEDT derives from {{cog|tbq-pro|*tsju||water; [[liquid]]; [[bodily fluid]]}}.
*{{zh-ref|Baxter and Sagart (2014)}}, employing evidence from the {{w|Proto-Min}} form of the Min colloquial variant {{m|zh|沝}}, reconstructs the latter ''*turʔ'' and thereby reconstructs {{cog|och|-}} ''*s.turʔ'', and compares it to {{cog|tbq-pro|*twəj||to flow; to [[suppurate]]}}, which is likely related to what STEDT notates as {{m+|tbq-pro|*s-turʔ|*m-t(w)əy-n ~ m-ti-s|t=water; fluid; to [[soak]]; to be wet}} (STEDT). ''*s.turʔ'' was then followed by an Eastern dialectal variant, ''*s.tujʔ'', which leads to Early Middle Chinese ''*sywijX''.
*Like {{zh-ref|Gong (1995)}}, {{zh-ref|Sagart (2017)}} compares {{zh-l|*水}} to {{cog|bo|ཆུ|tr=chu}}, but he also compares it to {{cog|brx|दै|tr=dwi}}, {{cog|lus|tui}}, {{cog|kar-pro|*thejᴬ}}, for which he tentatively  derives from {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*s-turʔ}}.
** Meanwhile STEDT derives said non-Sinitic items from {{cog|tbq-pro|*s-turʔ|*m-t(w)əy-n ~ m-ti-s}}. 
* Handel thinks {{zh-l|*水}} is unlikely to be related to {{m+|tbq-pro|*tsju}} and {{m+|tbq-pro|*m-t(w)əj-n ~ m-ti-s}} because of phonological issues (STEDT).

